      "content": "The 2-hour gap is the only rule you need to know, and it works because clarithromycin blocks the liver enzymes that break down simvastatin, so taking them too close together can spike your cholesterol dangerously.\nDon't worry about \"messing things up\" if you follow this simple schedule; your liver will process the drugs perfectly fine when spaced correctly.\nJust stick to the timing, and you'll be fine.",
